        img(src="img/proyectos/vivienda.png", alt="")
      h3 In this report, data from the income and housing modules of the ENAHO from 2015 to 2021 was cross-referenced to analyze how housing subsidies are distributed in the country. A high qualitative deficit was evidenced: while self-construction predominates in the D/E sectors, those who receive state benefits are the ones with higher incomes.
